=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Overviews_Operators_ex27 ===

DESCRIPTION: A dark pure_tone sound, with fm_or_inharmonic oscillator character around 265 Hz, featuring punchy attack and dynamic envelope, with dynamic spectral movement, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally simple.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: dark
  crest_factor_db: dynamic
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: simple
  spectral_flux_normalized: dynamic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 265.4303
  harmonic_decay_rate: 1.9818
  harmonic_regularity: 0.0135
  pitch_clarity: 63.4119
  inharmonicity: 0.2109
  type: fm_or_inharmonic
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -9.1152
  resonance_freq: 796.7285

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: Operators Example 27
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Overviews/Operators.html
// Tags: Operators, Overviews
// ---
// --- Example 27 ---
(
{
    var a, b;
    a = FSinOsc.ar(800);
    b = FSinOsc.ar(XLine.kr(200,500,5));
    ((a * b) + a) * 0.125
}.play)
